         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">27/12/66 ¶  ¶ This day, dear Prof. Balfour, I receive with the arrival of the Great Britain bill of loading of the case with plants you so kindly sent. I shall not receive it before the mail closes, b...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">66.12.27a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Balfour</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh, J. H. Balfour correspondence, vol. X, f. 271.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27/12/66</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day, dear Prof. Balfour, I receive with the arrival of the Great Britain bill of loading of the case with plants you so kindly sent. I shall not receive it before the mail closes, but meanwhile give you my cordial thanks for your libera[l] goodness.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Mesembryanthemum which safely reached you I have described a few months ago as M. tegens.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B66.10.01, p. 157.</p>
               </note> It covers immense patches of low flats with an uninterrupted carpet &amp; I use it for edging[s]. It comes near some Cape species &amp; has the flowers (staminodia &amp;c) almost of M. geminatum. I restrict Dracaena to D. draco &amp; any species with horny albumen &amp; short embryo &amp; include in <name key="Cordyline">Cordyline</name> all the species with oily amygdaline albumen &amp; long embryo.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My fifth volume of fragmenta will reach you in a few weeks.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your ever regardful &amp; grateful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
